
<purchabr>MIM</purchabr> TO ACQUIRE STAKE IN GERMAN COPPER PRODUCER
    FRANKFURT, March 16 - <purchaser>Mount Isa Mines Holding Ltd</purchaser> <status>plans to
acquire</status> a 30 pct stake in Europe's largest primary <acqbus>copper</acqbus>
producer, <acquired>Norddeutsche Affinerie AG</acquired>, a spokesman for
Metallgesellschaft AG said.
    <purchabr>MIM</purchabr> intends to take <seller>Preussag AG</seller>'s total 20 pct share in the
copper producer in exchange for some three pct of <status>MIM</status>'s share
capital. <purchabr>MIM</purchabr> will also take another 10 pct now held by <seller>Degussa
AG</seller>, reducing <sellerabr>Degussa</sellerabr>'s share to 30 pct from 40.
Metallgesellschaft's share will remain at 40 pct.
    The move is subject to approval of the federal cartel
office and supervisory boards of the companies involved.
